description:
&lt;p&gt;An opportunity has become available for enthusiastic Registered Nurses to join one of ACE’s integrated care teams. Do you have experience within the healthcare sector? Are you looking to expand your knowledge and learn new skills or develop current ones? Would you like to be part of a busy integrated nursing service within the local community? If so this could be the role for you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are able to offer both full and part time hours based in either Colchester or Tendring locality.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As part of this role you will be required to undertake various duties/tasks. This would be to support the delivery of person centered care in the community. Enabling individuals to remain at home safely, avoiding unnecessary admissions to hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will work in collaboration with Advanced Nurse Practitioners and Therapists as well as other outside agencies such as GP’s, social care and St Helena Hospice to promote independence and to collaboratively effectively manage long term conditions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This will enable us to meet the needs of patients within their own homes and the residential care setting, working to support the Care Closer to home contract.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Some of the duties include:- (Full training to be provided)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Diabetes management&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Various wound care procedures&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Pressure Ulcer Prevention (including ordering of equipment)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Venepuncture&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Catheterisation&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Participating in patient’s rehabilitation care planning&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Leg ulcer management (Compression therapy)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Carrying out Full Holistic assessments&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Implementing clinical care plans&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It is essential that you are a car driver as you will be expected to travel across the North East Essex area. You need to have a flexible approach and possess good interpersonal skills and have the ability to work autonomously as well as part of a team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The hours of work are shifts covering a 24 hour period.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; For external applicants this post attracts an additional payment of £1,000, to be paid in 2 installments:&lt;br /&gt; • £500 to be paid on completion of probation &lt;br /&gt; • £500 on completion of 12 months employment&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you would like further information about the role, informal enquiries can be made to either Steph Stevens 07939 479598 stephanie.stevens@acecic.nhs.uk / Nikki Smith Nikki.smith2@nhs.net for the Tendring area or Clara Gilfillan 07747 766561 clara.gilfillan@acecic.nhs.uk for the Colchester area.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post is classified as Regulated Activity and is exempt from the Rehabilitation of Offenders Act 1974 (Exceptions) Order 1975 (as amended in 2013). You must therefore disclose on your application form all convictions,    cautions, youth cautions and youth conditional cautions, which are not protected. Guidance and criteria on the filtering of cautions and convictions and what you must therefore disclose on your application form can be found on the Disclosure and Barring Service website. If you are offered the post we will need to obtain a satisfactory Disclosure and Barring Service (DBS) Check for you. You will also be expected to join the DBS update service and renew this annually, the cost of which will be reimbursed to you. You are advised to read the attached leaflet regarding the Disclosure and Barring Service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;ACE is commissioned to provide a number of services including Community based health services (Care Closer to Home). We have been advised by North East Essex Clinical Commissioning Group that this contract will be provided by another organisation after 30th June 2021. This is not as a reflection of ACE but due to the Commissioner wanting to make changes to the way the service is delivered. At the present time we don’t know who the new provider will be but the CCG is working to determine this by the end of 2020. This change does not affect our ability to recruit and should you be employed at the end of June 2021 you will transfer to the new provider on the same terms and conditions. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Working for ACE puts you right at the heart of all North Essex has to offer. If you are looking to re-locate to the area then we may be able to help with your moving costs. Further information can be found in the Relocation policy &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Within Tendring you have 60kms of beautiful coastline including Blue Flag beaches, the gentile charm of Frinton and the more bustling Clacton – one of the driest places to live in the UK!  Within a stone’s throw of Tendring is Colchester – Britain’s oldest recorded town and now one of its fastest growing with a range of recreational facilities to match. The jewel in the crown of its historic past is its Norman castle, built on Roman foundations. A wealth of new homes is complemented by an equally broad selection of character homes in the plethora of picture-postcards villages that surround the town. The likes of Sible Hedingham, Finchingfield and Dedham (the latter being the heart of Constable Country made famous by the artist John Constable) are much sought-after locations. In addition North Essex boasts several nationally acclaimed schools, including Colchester Royal Grammar School and Colchester County High School for Girls. London Stansted Airport is less than an hour’s drive away while all the attractions of London itself are within easy reach. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
